        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Shamans can't charm stuff in fear, they will be less efficient.  They also have no escape spells as Xell said(no FD is a biggie), which means if they screwed up they'll die, or be forced to gate, in which case it is utterly impossible to break back into fear(no FD = near impossibility getting from portal to Nwall).</P><P>However, a shaman with his epic can probably solo two mobs at the same time.  I know they can certainly solo two krups, and fear mobs are about as tough as krups(some are weaker, some stronger).  That doesn't mean that they can solo Fear more effectively, though, because Fear as far as zones go is quite unique, and requires a person with the FD and /q out ability to solo effectively.  </P><P>So there you have it - necros are probably better soloers in Fear than shamans, though both classes can do it.  Shamans can do it till they screw up, in which case it's over and they have to gate out.  Necros can solo Fear indefinitely.  He can simply FD if he gets into trouble.  I'd imagine, though, that a druid/wizzie too is probably capable of soloing fear.  He can bind himself at nwall, and mem a personal portal spell as an escape spell, and probably would do fine now that mobs don't summon.</P><P>The big thing here is the change with mob summons.  Before that, I have no doubt that a shaman would supercede a necro in being able to solo fear.  A necro simply can't handle summon mobs in a fully spawned fear that double for 140+.  But a necro is BUILT to handle non-summoning outdoor mobs, especially since many mobs in fear can't outrun jboots.(scarelings can, and they're still dangerous)  As long as you don't miss pull a golem or aggro draco/CT in case they're up, you'll probably be fine.<BR> <BR>Guess we'll wait and see if Verant nerfs this.  Not that it would matter much, since people who can solo Fear will most likely have no use for blighted at any case, and the other class armors are all no drop.  </P><P>The more important thing though is that the new no summoning rules is opening up new frontiers for us necros.  That's probably because the #1 hinderance that prevents necros from becoming as good soloers as shamans is the summoning for 51+ mobs.  We can solo juggs and dragons too, if they didn't summon.  But as it is, we have our advantages, and shamans have theirs.  A necro would be hard pressed to solo any dragon in WW, and it'd be impossible to solo a jugg or anything else of that caliber as a necro, period.  Still, if this was intended, I finally see VI going in the right direction.</P><P></P><P>Etadanik the Redeemed</font></td>
