        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>What people don't understand is how many pre-requisites have to be met be met in order for a shaman to pull off these "epic" solo feats.</P><P>1) They <b>must</b> be level 60 (anything less is absolutely insufficient).</P><P>2) They <b>must</b> have a jaundiced bone bracer and epic spear.</P><P>3) They <b>must</b> have torpor, and malo.</P><P>-and-</P><P>4) They <b>must</b> have roughly 1000 ac, unbuffed along with ~170 wis.</P><P>The people who meet all of these criteria make up about 1 to 2% of the shaman population. And the shamans who miss even one or two of those points aren't worth a flip compared to a necro in a lot of solo situations.</P><P>As far as this POF thing is concerned... even a shaman who met every one of those requirements could <b>not</b> duplicate what Xell did. The shamans on the crucible are too proud to say it. But they know it just as well as I do.</P><P>They would get run out of town on the first bad pull. Maybe they could do two mobs at once. But three at once would be the end of their POF tour. Time to hit the cazic potion. *click*</P><P>My main is a level 55 shaman (with JBB). And I've duoed with a necro since level nine. All these stories of shamans soloing sebilite juggernauts and WW dragons are real nice. But take your average 53-59 shaman and pit him against your average 53-59 necro. And the necro is just a much more well-rounded solo character.</P><P>I guess it goes to show that the grass <b>is</b> greener on the other side of the fence. Because I'm in the process of building my shaman up so i can strip him down, sell his shit to start an iksar necro.</P><P>Why am I doing this? It's because I'm never gonna fall into that "uber 2%" with my shaman (given my small guild and lack of connections). And I've seen firsthand how gimp I am in comparison to my necro partner in like 70-80% of the places we go.</P><P>So keep on comparing yourselves to these super duper mega-shamans who solo the crypt in sebilis. But all Im trying to tell you is that those shamans are the <b>exception</b>, and not the rule.</P><P></P><P>Edited by - Christabel on 08/08/2001  00:53:29</font></td>
